A two-year-old boy will receive revolutionary treatment for his rare disease after a mystery benefactor donated £40,000. 

Kat Musgrove had 30 days to find £140,000 so her son Kian could fly to the U.S and have his neuroblastoma treated.

She was struggling to raise the final bit of money until an anonymous donor from Luxembourg stepped in.  

